---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME } from '../config/site';
---

<Layout
	title={`Privacy - ${SITE_NAME}`}
	description="Privacy policy for DevDock, including what data is collected, how it is used, and how to contact the developer."
>
	<section class="section section--light pageHero">
		<div class="container narrow">
			<p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
			<h1 class="displayHero">Privacy policy</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				This policy explains how {SITE_NAME} ("DevDock", "we", "us") handles information when you use the app and this
				website. If you have questions, contact us using the details at the end of this page.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section section--light pageBody">
		<div class="container narrow">
			<article class="prose" data-reveal>
				<h2>Summary</h2>
				<p>
					DevDock is designed to run locally on your computer. By default, it does not require an account and it does
					not upload your project files to our servers.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>DevDock runs locally and manages local services on your machine</li>
					<li>Your project files stay on your device</li>
					<li>We do not sell personal information</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Information we collect</h2>
				<p>
					The information we handle falls into three categories: information you provide, information created on your
					device as part of normal operation, and optional diagnostics if you choose to send them.
				</p>
				<h3>Information you provide</h3>
				<ul>
					<li>Service settings you configure inside DevDock</li>
					<li>Text you enter into tools inside DevDock (for example, HTTP request data)</li>
					<li>Support messages you send to us and any attachments you choose to include</li>
				</ul>
				<h3>Local files created by DevDock</h3>
				<p>
					DevDock keeps service files, logs, and configuration files in a local folder on your computer so you can find
					them easily. This is part of normal operation. These files stay on your device unless you choose to share
					them.
				</p>
				<h3>Optional diagnostics</h3>
				<p>
					DevDock may display error details locally. If you contact support, you may choose to share logs or screenshots
					to help us understand the issue. We only receive what you send us.
				</ul>

				<h2>How we use information</h2>
				<p>We use information for the following purposes:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Provide and improve DevDock features</li>
					<li>Help you troubleshoot issues when you request support</li>
					<li>Maintain the security and stability of the app</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>What we do not do</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>We do not sell your personal information</li>
					<li>We do not read your files outside of what DevDock needs to run the services you enable</li>
					<li>We do not upload your project files to our servers by default</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Sharing and third parties</h2>
				<p>
					DevDock does not share your information with third parties for advertising. We may share information only in
					these situations:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>With your consent</strong> when you choose to send us logs or other data for support</li>
					<li><strong>For legal reasons</strong> if we are required to comply with a valid legal process</li>
					<li><strong>To protect safety</strong> if needed to prevent fraud, abuse, or security issues</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Data retention</h2>
				<p>
					Local service files and logs remain on your device until you delete them. If you contact support, we retain
					your message and any attachments as long as needed to respond, maintain records, and improve the product. You
					can request deletion of support communications by contacting us.
				</p>

				<h2>Security</h2>
				<p>
					We take reasonable steps to protect information you send us. No method of transmission or storage is 100
					percent secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security. You are responsible for protecting access to your
					device and for reviewing what you choose to share with support.
				</p>

				<h2>Children's privacy</h2>
				<p>
					DevDock is not directed to children under 13 and we do not knowingly collect personal information from
					children under 13. If you believe a child provided information to us, contact us and we will take steps to
					delete it.
				</p>

				<h2>Your rights</h2>
				<p>
					Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete personal information we have
					about you. If you contact us, we will respond within a reasonable time.
				</p>

				<h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
				<p>
					We may update this policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will update the date below and
					publish the revised policy on this page.
				</p>

				<h2>Contact</h2>
				<p>
					For privacy questions or requests, contact:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Email:</strong> privacy@example.com</li>
					<li><strong>Developer:</strong> Your Name</li>
				</ul>

				<p class="fine">
					Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
					.
				</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.pageHero {
		padding-bottom: 32px;
	}
	.eyebrow {
		margin: 0 0 12px;
		font-size: 13px;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
		font-weight: 500;
	}
	.narrow {
		max-width: 720px;
	}
	.pageBody {
		padding-top: 0;
	}
	.prose h2 {
		font-family: var(--font-display);
		font-size: 28px;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.15;
		margin: 36px 0 12px;
		color: var(--c-text-dark);
	}
	.prose h2:first-child {
		margin-top: 0;
	}
	.prose p,
	.prose ul {
		font-size: 17px;
		line-height: 1.55;
		letter-spacing: -0.3px;
		color: var(--c-text-subtle);
	}
	.prose ul {
		padding-left: 1.2em;
	}
	.prose .fine {
		margin-top: 48px;
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
	}
</style>
